20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhen%20only%2034%25%20of%20corporate%20heads%20said%20they%20expected%20their%20teams%20would%20be%20back%20IRL%20five%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20another%20sign%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-fears-job-cuts-employers-less-flexible-with-workers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERTO%20fights%3C%2Fa%3E%20aren't%20over%20and%20that%20some%20pandemic-era%20work%20norms%20might%20prove%20as%20ephemeral%20as%20social%20distancing%20and%20mask%20mandates%20on%20planes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Knopp%2C%20chair%20and%20CEO%20at%20KPMG%20US%2C%20said%20the%20survey%20results%20indicate%20that%20CEOs%20believe%20they%20can%20speed%20the%20development%20and%20mentoring%20of%20their%20employees%20when%20people%20are%20face%20to%20face%20more%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20he%20also%20told%20Business%20Insider%20%E2%80%94%20before%20Amazon's%20RTO%20announcement%20%E2%80%94%20that%20while%20the%20survey%20showed%20a%20clear%20swing%20in%20sentiment%2C%20that%20hasn't%20necessarily%20translated%20into%20widespread%20action.%20Even%20if%20offices%20begin%20to%20look%20more%20like%20they%20once%20did%2C%20Knopp%20said%2C%20many%20workers%20will%20enjoy%20more%20autonomy%20than%20they%20had%20in%20the%20before%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20still%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20That%20might%20look%20like%20working%20fewer%20evening%20hours%2C%20showing%20up%20a%20little%20later%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20or%20not%20at%20all%20on%20weekends%2C%20Knopp%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d1ac96f-f135-40dd-a159-3a87960cf709%5C%22%3EMost%20CEOs%20expect%20hybrid%20will%20fade%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20survey%2C%20which%20was%20conducted%20between%20mid-July%20and%20late%20August%2C%2017%25%20of%20chiefs%20predicted%20their%20people%20would%20work%20in%20hybrid%20setups%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20and%20only%204%25%20said%20they%20expected%20their%20workers%20to%20be%20fully%20remote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20definitely%20a%20strong%20sentiment%20to%20want%20more%20in-person%20interaction%20%E2%80%94%20more%20human%20connection%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20notion%20that%20that%20can%20help%20both%20employees%20and%20employers%2C%26quot%3B%20Knopp%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20challenge%20around%20splitting%20time%20between%20home%20and%20work%20is%20that%2C%20unlike%20being%20in%20the%20office%20or%20remote%20full%20time%2C%20there's%20not%20one%20agreed-upon%20setup%2C%20he%20commented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20complicated%20or%20complex%20working%20environment%20to%20actually%20orchestrate%20or%20pull%20off%20is%20hybrid%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20people%20at%20the%20start%20of%20their%20careers%20might%20want%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-workers-want-flexibility-fair-pay-survey-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20some%20surveys%20have%20shown.%20But%20working%20parents%2C%20for%20example%2C%20might%20want%20more%20time%20at%20home%2C%20Knopp%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20those%20types%20of%20concerns%20could%20lead%20to%20attrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20have%20people%20back%20in%20the%20office%20more%2C%20do%20I%20take%20a%20risk%20that%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20the%20talent%20that%20I%20want%3F%26quot%3B%20Knopp%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20calibrate%20all%20these%20risks%20constantly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20an%20organization%20starts%20to%20lose%20key%20people%2C%20he%20said%2C%20leaders%20might%20walk%20back%20RTO%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttrition%20is%20one%20concern%20that%20Stanford%20economist%20Nicholas%20Bloom%20previously%20shared%20with%20BI.%20His%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-return-to-office-mandate-bosses-morale-productivity-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20demanding%20employees%20show%20up%20more%20could%20drive%20away%20some%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20study%20involving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FTrip.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrip.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Bloom%20and%20his%20collaborators%20found%20that%20when%20the%20travel%20company%20cut%20its%20in-office%20requirement%20to%20three%20days%20a%20week%20from%20five%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20workers%20quitting%20dropped%20by%20about%20one-third.%20That%20can%20be%20good%20news%20for%20companies%20because%20many%20times%2C%20the%20ones%20who%20leave%20are%20the%20ones%20bosses%20are%20sorry%20to%20see%20go%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOften%20the%20best%20employees%20leave%20as%20they%20have%20the%20best%20outside%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a9918096-80f4-4df9-ac91-502bee0300da%5C%22%3EGenAI%20will%20require%20that%20workers%20add%20skills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20KPMG%20US%20findings%20also%20highlighted%20that%20many%20bosses%20are%20worried%20about%20the%20aging%20workforce%20and%20the%20risks%20that%20brings%20to%20recruiting%2C%20keeping%20employees%2C%20and%20overall%20culture.%20About%20one%20in%20three%20CEOs%20said%20retirements%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20skilled%20replacements%20would%20have%20a%20big%20effect%20on%20their%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20come%20in%20a%20year%20in%20which%20Gen%20Z%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glassdoor.com%2Fblog%2Fworkplace-trends-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eovertaken%20baby%20boomers%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20full-time%20US%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECEOs%20also%20said%20the%20rise%20of%20technologies%20like%20generative%20artificial%20intelligence%20will%20necessitate%20that%20workers%20get%20training.%20Eight%20in%2010%20chiefs%20agreed%20that%20companies%20should%20invest%20in%20skills%20development%20and%20%26quot%3Blifelong%20learning%26quot%3B%20in%20communities%20to%20maintain%20access%20to%20talent%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20seven%20in%2010%20CEOs%20said%20GenAI%20wouldn't%20have%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20at%20their%20company%20%E2%80%94%20contrary%20to%20concerns%20that%20the%20technology%20will%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-threaten-jobs-of-coders-who-dont-shift-their-focus-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob-killer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20fact%2C%2027%25%20of%20top%20bosses%20said%20GenAI%20would%20create%20more%20jobs%20than%20it%20destroys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnopp%20said%20AI%20is%20already%20taking%20over%20some%20routine%20tasks%20and%20freeing%20workers%20to%20do%20other%20things.%20It%20can%20also%20help%20compensate%20for%20what's%20lost%20when%20workers%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20mitigate%20it%20through%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20mitigate%20it%20through%20upskilling%2C%20reskilling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b272c792-3f37-4216-9eb4-5a92a8c342ea%5C%22%3EMore%20reasons%20to%20invest%20in%20tech%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20found%20that%20those%20in%20charge%20have%20big%20hopes%20for%20GenAI.%20CEOs%20are%20looking%20to%20the%20technology%20to%20boost%20efficiency%20and%20productivity%20by%20automating%20routine%20tasks%2C%20helping%20train%20workers%2C%20and%20promoting%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20seven%20in%2010%20leaders%20said%20GenAI%20is%20a%20top%20investment%20priority%2C%20especially%20in%20IT%2C%20sales%20and%20marketing%2C%20and%20finance%20and%20accounting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20investments%20around%20the%20tech%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20more%20defensive.%20Only%2054%25%20of%20CEOs%20reported%20that%20their%20companies%20were%20%26quot%3Bwell-prepared%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20cyber%20attack.%20Just%20more%20than%20one%20in%20three%20said%20they%20weren't%20sure%20whether%20their%20company's%20cyber%20defenses%20could%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20pace%26quot%3B%20with%20AI.%20About%20seven%20in%2010%20said%20they%20were%20increasing%20spending%20on%20cybersecurity%20to%20help%20fend%20off%20AI%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20all%20the%20changes%20leaders%20expect%20AI%20will%20bring%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20for%20workers%20to%20become%20proficient%20with%20it%2C%20Knopp%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20that%20have%20generative%20AI%20and%20AI%20skills%20are%20going%20to%20have%20a%20big%20advantage%20in%20the%20marketplace%20over%20those%20that%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-souring-on-hybrid-work-expect-full-rto-kpmg-says-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726651742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e9efb3cfb7f307e57284cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-souring-on-hybrid-work-expect-full-rto-kpmg-says-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CEOs%20of%20big%20US%20companies%20are%20increasingly%20expecting%20to%20end%20hybrid%20work%20setups%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20according%20to%20KPMG%20US.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-souring-on-hybrid-work-expect-full-rto-kpmg-says-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election'%20cleared%20by%20Union%20Cabinet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726651718000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113454142%2Cimgsize-1501680.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fone-nation-one-election-cleared-by-union-cabinet