%20commissioned%20by%20Hearst%20Publications%2C%20up%20to%2070%25%20of%20a%20company's%20workforce%20can%20be%20either%20going%20through%20a%20divorce%20or%20impacted%20by%20a%20close%20colleague%20experiencing%20one.%20This%20means%20a%20divorce%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffriends-divorce-affect-me-grief-loss-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyours%20or%20a%20colleague's%3C%2Fa%3E)%20will%20probably%20happen%20to%20you%20if%20it%20hasn't%20already.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20even%20counting%20separations%20and%20the%20end%20of%20long-term%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20my%20seniority%2C%20I%20couldn't%20take%20time%20off%20to%20cope.%20So%2C%20instead%2C%20I'm%20sad%20to%20say%20that%20I%20turned%20my%20workroom%20into%20a%20toxic%20environment%20with%20daily%20tirades%20about%20my%20divorce.%20I%20was%20often%20scattered%2C%20unreliable%2C%20and%20absent.%20I%20sometimes%20burst%20into%20tears%20with%20no%20warning.%20When%20the%20client%20left%20the%20agency%20over%20many%20factors%2C%20I%20wondered%20how%20much%20my%20poor%20performance%20had%20played%20a%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20fired%20soon%20after%20and%20couldn't%20bring%20myself%20to%20seek%20out%20work%20for%2018%20months.%20I%20almost%20didn't%20return%20to%20my%20industry.%20Neglecting%20divorce%20is%20bad%20for%20people%20and%20company%20morale%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheparentspromise.org.uk%2Fhr-initiative%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epotentially%20disastrous%20for%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2237c959c9-e32b-4946-8134-0e08d03b3d9d%5C%22%3EI%20added%20my%20divorce%20to%20my%20LinkedIn%202%20weeks%20ago%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDivorce%20hits%20different%20people%20differently.%20It%20took%20until%20last%20year%20before%20I%20could%20say%20I'd%20finally%20processed%20it%20%E2%80%94%20in%20its%20entirety.%20And%20I%20added%20it%20to%20my%20LinkedIn%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20two%2