e%20public%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EBret%20Taylor%2C%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Board%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%20is%20best%20known%20for%20his%20time%20as%20Facebook's%20CTO%20and%20for%20helping%20to%20lead%20the%20team%20that%20created%20Google%20Maps.%20He%20joined%20OpenAI's%20board%20in%202023%20after%20the%20failed%20attempt%20to%20push%20out%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20and%20has%20since%20been%20leading%20the%20effort%20to%20rebuild%20the%20company's%20board%20and%20reassure%20investors%20and%20consumers%20alike%20that%20OpenAI%20is%20in%20good%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20recruited%20a%20veritable%20who's%20who%20of%20tech%20and%20policy%20talent%20to%20help%20steer%20the%20rapidly%20growing%20company%2C%20including%20former%20U.S.%20Secretary%20of%20the%20Treasury%20Larry%20Summers%2C%20Instacart%20CEO%20Fidji%20Simo%2C%20and%20former%20CEO%20of%20the%20Bill%20and%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20Nicole%20Seligman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EAdam%20D'Angelo%2C%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Board%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Facebook%20executive%20and%20founder%20of%20Quora%20was%20one%20of%20four%20OpenAI%20board%20members%20who%20voted%20to%20fire%20Sam%20Altman%20last%20November.%20But%20he%20was%20also%20the%20only%20board%20member%20to%20stay%20with%20the%20company%20following%20Altman's%20return.%20In%20fact%2C%20during%20the%20negotiations%20to%20reinstate%20Altman%2C%20D'Angelo%20was%20apparently%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fai%2Fadam-dangelo-openai-board-19ab00ee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20only%20board%20director%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20all%20sides%20could%20agree%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20longtime%20fixture%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20power%20circles%2C%20D'Angelo%20has%20continued%20to%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20shaping%20OpenAI's%20future.%20He%20has%20helped%20to%20build%20open%20lines%20of%20communication%20between%20employees%20and%20management%20and%20brought%20a%20sense%20of%20stability%20to%20the%20rapidly%20expanding%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2289a13355-a34e-4d96-9d16-efab212eb0f4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Challenges%20and%20Government%20Outreach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EAndrea%20Appella%2C%20Associate%20General%20Counsel%20Europe%2C%20Middle%20East%2C%20Asia%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrea%20Appella%20is%20a%20leading%20expert%20on%20competition%20and%20regulatory%20law.%20He%20previously%20served%20as%20Head%20of%20Global%20Competition%20at%20Netflix%20and%20Deputy%20General%20Counsel%20at%2021st%20Century%20Fox.%20He%20is%20OpenAI's%20first%20legal%20hire%20in%20London%20and%20will%20oversee%20the%20company's%20strategy%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20regulatory%20issues%20and%20antitrust%20inquiries%20in%20Europe%20and%20beyond.%20Regulatory%20scrutiny%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20existential%20threats%20for%20the%20growing%20company%20as%20policymakers%20race%20to%20put%20guardrails%20on%20the%20nascent%20AI%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowhere%20have%20lawmakers%20been%20more%20aggressive%20than%20in%20Europe%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Feu-countries-back-landmark-artificial-intelligence-rules-2024-05-21%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eleading%20the%20world%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20AI%20regulations.%20That%20makes%20Appella's%20role%20as%20the%20company's%20top%20legal%20representative%20in%20Europe%20one%20of%20the%20most%20crucial%20positions%20in%20determining%20the%20company's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EHaidee%20Schwartz%2C%20Associate%20General%20Counsel%2C%20Competition%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20spent%20that%20last%20year%20beefing%20up%20its%20legal%20team%20as%20it%20faces%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F05%2Ftechnology%2Fnvidia-microsoft-openai-antitrust-doj-ftc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emultiple%20antitrust%20probes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Schwartz%2C%20who%20joined%20the%20company%20in%202023%2C%20knows%20more%20about%20antitrust%20enforcement%20than%20almost%20anyone%20on%20Earth%2C%20having%20seen%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20issue%20during%20her%20storied%20legal%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202017%20and%202019%2C%20she%20served%20as%20the%20Acting%20Deputy%20Director%20of%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Competition%20at%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%2C%20one%20of%20the%20agencies%20currently%20investigating%20OpenAI's%20dominance%20within%20the%20AI%20industry.%20Schwartz%20also%20advised%20clients%20on%20merger%20review%20and%20antitrust%20enforcement%20as%20a%20partner%20at%20law%20firm%20Akin%20Gump.%20She'll%20likely%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20helping%20OpenAI%20navigate%20the%20potential%20minefield%20of%20antitrust%20scrutiny%20as%20the%20company%20expands%20its%20foothold%20in%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EHeather%20Whitney%2C%20Copyright%20Counsel%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhitney%20joined%20OpenAI%20last%20January%20after%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20filed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F27%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fnew-york-times-open-ai-microsoft-lawsuit.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emajor%20copyright%20lawsuit%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20company%20and%20its%20corporate%20backer%2C%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-lawsuit-copyrighted-data-train-chatgpt-court-tech-ai-news-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20legal%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E%20brought%20by%20publishers%20alleging%20that%20OpenAI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-testimony-legal-filing-sheds-light-on-openais-strategy-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eviolated%20copyright%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20used%20books%20and%20journalistic%20work%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20models.%20The%20outcomes%20of%20these%20lawsuits%2C%20which%20raise%20unprecedented%20questions%20about%20intellectual%20property%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%20will%20be%20essential%20in%20determining%20OpenAI%20prospects%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhitney%20comes%20to%20OpenAI%20from%20the%20law%20firm%20Morrison%20Foerster%2C%20where%20she%20focused%20on%20novel%20copyright%20issues%20related%20to%20AI%20and%20served%20on%20the%20firm's%20AI%20Steering%20Committee.%20Morrison%20Foerster%20is%20one%20of%20the%20many%20outside%20law%20firms%20representing%20OpenAI%20and%20Whitney%20had%20been%20working%20with%20the%20company%20before%20being%20hired%20outright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20an%20expert%20on%20intellectual%20property%20law%20and%20AI%20and%20has%20lectured%20and%20done%20research%20on%20the%20subject%20at%20Harvard%20Law%20School%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20Law%20School.%20She%20is%20also%20currently%20completing%20a%20PhD%20in%20copyright%2C%20free%20speech%20theory%2C%20and%20AI%20at%20NYU.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EChan%20Park%2C%20Head%20of%20U.S.%20and%20Canada%20Policy%20and%20Partnerships%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20last%20November%20registered%20Park%20as%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnewsletters%2Fpolitico-influence%2F2023%2F11%2F17%2Fopenai-registers-to-lobby-00127874%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efirst%20in-house%20lobbyist%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Park%20previously%20served%20as%20senior%20director%20of%20congressional%20affairs%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20is%20now%20helping%20to%20lead%20OpenAI's%20outreach%20to%20lawmakers.%20Over%20the%20last%20year%20OpenAI%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Ftransactional%2Fopenai-expands-lobbying-efforts-hiring-former-us-senator-2024-03-12%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C