s.%20Getting%20biblical%20about%20in-office%20attendance%20is%20outdated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-commandment-office-work-shibboleth-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20'We%20Lost%20Her'%3A%20A%20Smartphone%20Epidemic%20Is%20Ruining%20Europe's%20New%20Generation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-07%2Fmobile-phone_650x400_81501483347.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20lost%20her%2C%20and%20she%20lost%20her%20childhood.%26quot%3B%20These%20were%20the%20words%20of%20Amanda%20Miller%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20a%2015-year-old%20girl%20who%20has%20been%20in%20the%20hospital%20for%20a%20year%2C%20undergoing%20treatment%20for%20acute%20mental%20health%20problems.%20Smartphone%20addiction%20has%20torn%20the%20teenager's%20world%20apart.%20Amanda%20now%20campaigns%20to%20ban%20the%20device%20for%20children%20in%20British%20schools.%20The%20Labour%20government%20is%20currently%20considering%20a%20ban%20on%20smartphones%20for%20children%20under%2016%20in%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20a%20TV%20channel%2C%20Amanda%20revealed%20that%20she%20reluctantly%20bought%20her%20daughter%20a%20smartphone%20for%20her%2010th%20birthday%2C%20a%20decision%20she%20now%20regrets.%20Her%20daughter%20quickly%20became%20obsessed%20with%20the%20device.%20%26quot%3BShe%20would%20come%20home%20from%20school%20and%20lock%20herself%20in%20her%20room%20with%20her%20phone.%20We%20completely%20lost%20her.%20Her%20mental%20health%20deteriorated-she%20started%20self-harming%2C%20became%20depressed%2C%20and%20suicidal%20to%20the%20point%20where%20she%20stopped%20eating.%20Eventually%2C%20she%20ended%20up%20in%20the%20hospital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmanda%20pleads%20with%20the%20UK%20Government%20to%20pass%20a%20law%20to%20help%20parents%20%26quot%3Bbring%20their%20children%20back%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Continental%20Epidemic%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20Amanda%2C%20millions%20of%20parents%20across%20Europe%20are%20increasingly%20vocal%20about%20the%20damaging%20effects%20of%20smartphones%20on%20their%20children.%20Parent-led%20movements%20are%20pushing%20for%20stricter%20screen%20time%20regulations%2C%20and%20even%20bans%20in%20schools%2C%20calling%20for%20comprehensive%20policies%20to%20protect%20the%20next%20generation's%20future.%20More%20than%2010%2C000%20mothers%20with%20young%20children%20in%20Spain%20have%20created%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20to%20inform%20one%20another%20of%20the%20state%20of%20their%20children's%20mental%20health%20and%20exchange%20tips%20on%20dealing%20with%20smartphone%20addiction.%20They%20want%20help%20from%20their%20government%20and%20demand%20legislation%20to%20ban%20smartphone%20use%20in%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20growing%20concern%20has%20sparked%20intense%20debates%20across%20Europe%20about%20how%20to%20address%20screen%20addiction%20among%20children.%20Movements%20advocating%20for%20phone-free%20schools%20are%20gaining%20momentum.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20legislation%2C%20some%20schools%20have%20started%20implementing%20smartphone-free%20classes%20and%20some%20others%20have%20completely%20banned%20phones%20in%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Crisis%20In%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20smartphone%20market%20has%20exploded%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20with%20no%20signs%20of%20slowing%20down.%20The%20youth%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20spend%20countless%20hours%20on%20their%20devices.%20Deloitte%20predicts%20that%20by%202026%2C%20India%20will%20be%20the%20second-largest%20smartphone%20market%2C%20surpassing%20one%20billion%20users%2C%20with%20rural%20areas%20driving%20sales%3Cbr%3E%5CnIndian%20youth%20are%20consumed%20by%20social%20media%20and%20smartphones%2C%20which%20have%20been%20linked%20to%20mental%20health%20problems%20like%20depression%2C%20anxiety%2C%20and%20social%20isolation.%20A%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%20(BCG)%20study%20reveals%20that%20half%20of%20Indian%20consumers%20pick%20up%20their%20phones%20out%20of%20habit%2C%20often%20without%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20in%20India%20warn%20that%20more%20comprehensive%20studies%20are%20needed%20to%20understand%20the%20full%20impact%20of%20smartphones%20on%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20both%20central%20and%20state%20governments%20have%20set%20up%20de-addiction%20and%20research%20centres%20focused%20on%20phone%20addiction.%20While%20the%20Indian%20government%20has%20taken%20steps%20to%20encourage%20responsible%20usage%2C%20more%20action%20is%20needed.%20In%202015%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Addiction%20of%20Technological%20Gadgets%20Bill%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20but%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20it%20was%20ever%20passed%20into%20law.%3Cbr%3E%5CnCan%20we%20expect%20teenagers%20to%20resist%20what%20adults%20cannot%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20millions%20of%20others%2C%20I%20rely%20on%20my%20smartphone%20for%20nearly%20every%20aspect%20of%20life-reading%2C%20writing%2C%20social%20media%2C%20internet%20browsing%2C%20and%20communication.%20I%20use%20it%20for%20payments%2C%20watching%20TV%2C%20and%20listening%20to%20music.%20With%20multiple%20OTT%20subscriptions%2C%20I%20have%20more%20content%20at%20my%20fingertips%20than%20I%20could%20ever%20use.%3Cbr%3E%5CnSo%2C%20is%20it%20fair%20to%20expect%20teenagers%20to%20limit%20their%20screen%20time%20and%20curb%20their%20dependence%20on%20smartphones%3F%20Some%20experts%20argue%20that%20banning%20smartphones%20in%20schools%20is%20ineffective%20and%20anti-technology.%20Instead%2C%20they%20believe%20students%20should%20be%20educated%20on%20responsible%20usage.%20Others%20warn%20that%20a%20ban%20might%20lead%20to%20covert%20smartphone%20use%20or%20smuggling%20of%20devices%20into%20classrooms.%20The%20focus%2C%20they%20say%2C%20should%20be%20on%20teaching%20children%20the%20benefits%20of%20responsible%20use%20and%20the%20dangers%20of%20overuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Scale%20Of%20The%20Problem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmanda%20Miller%20believes%20smartphones%20are%20%26quot%3Bkilling%20our%20children%2C%20killing%20their%20youth%2C%20destroying%20their%20mental%20health%26quot%3B.%20According%20to%20a%20study%20by%20the%20UK's%20broadcasting%20and%20telecommunications%20regulatory%20authority%2C%20Ofcom%2C%20%26quot%3Bby%20the%20age%20of%2012%2C%2097%25%20of%20children%20have%20their%20own%20mobile%20phones%26quot%3B.%20Studies%20have%20shown%20that%20increased%20screen%20time%20negatively%20impacts%20mental%20health%2C%20academic%20performance%2C%20and%20social%20skills.%20Adolescents%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20anxiety%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20sleep%20problems%20due%20to%20excessive%20smartphone%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202022%2C%20as%20much%20as%2068%25%20of%20the%20global%20population%20used%20smartphones%2C%20and%20over%2060%25%20of%20people%20in%20many%20countries%20admitted%20to%20being%20addicted%20to%20their%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmartphones%20have%20fuelled%20the%20rise%20of%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20allowing%20celebrities%20to%20connect%20with%20their%20young%20fans.%20Cristiano%20Ronaldo%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20reached%20one%20billion%20followers%20across%20social%20media%20platforms%20in%20September%2C%20with%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20his%20fanbase%20being%20young%20adults.%20Other%20youth%20icons%2C%20such%20as%20Selena%20Gomez%2C%20Justin%20Bieber%2C%20and%20Taylor%20Swift%2C%20also%20have%20millions%20of%20followers%2C%20reinforcing%20the%20hold%20smartphones%20have%20over%20young%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20smartphones%20offer%20practical%20benefits%20like%20communication%20and%20education%2C%20those%20opposing%20a%20ban%20argue%20that%20implementing%20it%20could%20brand%20Europe%20as%20anti-technology.%20However%2C%20the%20device's%20addictive%20nature%2C%20similar%20to%20gaming%20addiction%2C%20raises%20concerns.%20Last%20year%2C%20UNESCO%20called%20for%20a%20ban%20on%20smartphones%20in%20schools%2C%20and%20France%20has%20already%20enforced%20one.%20The%20UK%20is%20seriously%20considering%20banning%20smartphones%20for%20children%20aged%20five%20to%2016%20in%20schools%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20guidelines%20issued%20earlier%20this%20year%20supporting%20head%20teachers%20who%20prohibit%20mobile%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20British%20schools%20have%20already%20banned%20smartphones%20with%20great%20success%2C%20seeing%20improvements%20in%20academic%20performance%20and%20reduced%20distractions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20Experiment%20That%20Gives%20Hope%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%2010%20teenagers%20from%20a%20Manchester%20school%20participated%20in%20a%20five-day%20experiment%2C%20swapping%20their%20smartphones%20for%20basic%20mobile%20phones%20that%20only%20allowed%20calls%20and%20texts.%20These%20boys%20and%20girls%2C%20aged%2014%20to%2016%2C%20previously%20spent%20over%2012%20hours%20a%20day%20on%20their%20devices.%20While%20one%20participant%20demanded%20his%20smartphone%20back%2C%20the%20other%20nine%20completed%20the%20experiment.%20One%20boy%20reported%20better%20sleep%20and%20another%20girl%20shared%20that%20her%20relationship%20with%20her%20father%20improved%20as%20they%20spent%20more%20time%20talking.%20Though%20a%20small%20sample%2C%20the%20experiment%20suggested%20that%20life%20without%20smartphones%20is%20possible%20for%20even%20the%20most%20dependent%20teens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20British%20government%20contemplates%20the%20ban%20a%20school%20trust%20in%20England%20with%2035%2C000%20pupils%20has%20just%20announced%20it%20is%20banning%20smartphones%20in%20all%20its%2042%20schools%20in%20England.%20The%20trust%20hopes%20that%20the%20ban%20will%20lead%20to%20higher%20academic%20achievement%20and%20improve%20the%20mental%20health%20of%20its%20pupils.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726649700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-07%2Fmobile-phone_650x400_81501483347.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-a-smartphone-epidemic-is-destroying-europes-new-generation-6592345%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Parent-led%20movements%20are%20pushing%20for%20stricter%20screen%20time%20regulations%2C%20and%20even%20bans%20in%20schools%2C%20calling%20for%20comprehensive%20policies%20to%20protect%20the%20next%20generation's%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Italy's%20World%20Cup%20icon%20Schillaci%20dies%20aged%2059%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726649684000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_sport%2Feb7a%2Flive%2F5c0f70d0-6139-11ee-ac8c-9d18dbc280ea.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fsport%2Ffootball%2Farticles%2Fcqlvrp4nylwo%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Italian%20World%20Cup%20icon%20Salvatore%20Schillaci%2C%20the%20top%20scorer%20at%20the%201990%20World%20Cup%2C%20dies%20aged%2059.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A39%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https