0small%2C%20portable%20communication%20device%20that%20receives%20short%20messages%2C%20typically%20numeric%20or%20alphanumeric%2C%20over%20a%20radio%20frequency%20signal.%20Pagers%20were%20widely%20used%20before%20cell%20phones%20became%20popular.%20It%20was%20a%20crucial%20communication%20tool%2C%20especially%20for%20professionals%20like%20doctors%2C%20journalists%2C%20technicians%2C%20and%20managers.%20It%20allowed%20them%20to%20receive%20important%20messages%20and%20sound%20alerts%2C%20even%20in%20remote%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20pagers%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%20of%20a%20pager%20was%20straightforward%20yet%20efficient.%20When%20a%20message%20was%20sent%20via%20radio%20waves%2C%20the%20device%20would%20alert%20the%20user%20with%20a%20distinct%20beep.%20This%20prompt%20would%20then%20require%20the%20user%20to%20locate%20a%20nearby%20public%20or%20landline%20phone%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20pager%20was%20patented%20in%20the%20US%20in%201949%20by%20inventor%20Alfred%20Gross.%20The%20term%20%26quot%3Bpager%26quot%3B%20was%20officially%20registered%20in%201959%20by%20Motorola.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMotorola's%20first%20pager%2C%20the%20Pageboy%201%20created%20in%201964%2C%20allowed%20an%20audible%20alert%20to%20be%20sent%20by%20telephone%20before%20the%20technology%20was%20perfected%20and%20allowed%2C%20from%20the%2080s%2C%20to%20send%20written%20messages%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20technology%20progressed%2C%20pagers%20underwent%20significant%20improvements.%20The%20newer%20models%20were%20equipped%20with%20a%20small%20screen%2C%20enabling%20them%20to%20display%20short%20messages%20directly%20on%20the%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E61%20million%20pagers%20were%20in%20circulation%20worldwide%20in%201994%2C%20says%20an%20AFP%20report%20quoting%20US-based%20pager%20manufacturer%20Spok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20by%20the%201990s%2C%20mobile%20phones%20started%20to%20replace%20these%20little%20devices.%20The%20convenience%20of%20mobile%20phones%20quickly%20diminished%20the%20demand%20for%20pagers%2C%20and%20by%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20beepers%20had%20mostly%20vanished%20from%20public%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPagers%20continue%20to%20be%20used%20in%20some%20sectors%2C%20like%20hospitals%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Hezbollah%20members%20still%20use%20pagers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20cyberattack%20targeting%20Iran-backed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F3-grams-of-explosives-per-pager-israel-complex-op-to-hurt-hezbollah-6590229%5C%22%3EHezbollah%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20that%20pagers%2C%20which%20many%20assumed%20had%20become%20obsolete%2C%20were%20still%20in%20use%20by%20the%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pagers%20were%20used%20by%20Hezbollah%20fighters%20as%20a%20low-tech%20means%20of%20communication%20to%20evade%20Israeli%20location-tracking.%20Pagers%20use%20their%20own%20frequency%20and%20are%20therefore%20considered%20more%20reliable%20as%20they%20bypass%20mobile%20telephone%20networks%20that%20can%20be%20impacted%20by%20frequent%20interruptions%2C%20connection%20issues%20or%20can%20be%20intercepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20reports%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F3-grams-of-explosives-per-pager-israel-complex-op-to-hurt-hezbollah-6590229%5C%22%3EIsrael's%20Mossad%20spy%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20planted%20explosives%20inside%205%2C000%20pagers%20imported%20by%20Hezbollah%20months%20before%20Tuesday's%20detonations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lebanese%20security%20source%20told%20Reuters%20said%20the%20pagers%20were%20from%20Taiwan-based%20Gold%20Apollo%2C%20but%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20it%20did%20not%20manufacture%20the%20devices.%20It%20said%20they%20were%20made%20by%20a%20company%20called%20BAC%20which%20has%20a%20licence%20to%20use%20its%20brand%2C%20but%