a%3E%20has%20not%20paid%20Rs%20135.3%20crore%20in%20Provident%20Fund%20payments%20to%20employees%20for%20periods%20from%20April%202020%20to%20August%202023%2C%20the%20airline%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bseindia.com%2Fxml-data%2Fcorpfiling%2FAttachLive%2F8dd89219-377e-4e27-bd1c-099f9a0260f9.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edocument%20filed%20with%20the%20Bombay%20Stock%20Exchange%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20has%20also%20not%20paid%20Rs%20220%20crore%20in%20TDS%2C%20or%20tax%20deducted%20at%20source%2C%20from%20staff%20salaries%20for%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20in%20addition%20to%20nearly%20Rs%2072%20crore%20in%20TDS%20and%20Rs%2084.5%20crore%20in%20GST%2C%20or%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%2C%20payments%20that%20are%20disputed%2C%20as%20well%20as%20crores%20due%20in%20service%20tax%20(including%20interest)%20and%20customs%20and%20customs%20duties%20(including%20penalties%20for%20delay)%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20submitted%20by%20the%20airline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disputed%20TDS%20payments%20date%20from%20AY%202009%2F10%20to%20AY%202013%2F14%2C%20and%20the%20GST%20dues%20range%20from%20July%202017%20to%20March%202019.%20The%20oldest%20disputed%20figure%20is%20Rs%201.71%20crore%20in%20service%20tax%20from%20April%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENDTV%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20SpiceJet%20for%20a%20comment%20and%20this%20report%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20the%20company%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disputes%20and%20non-payments%20arise%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Bconstrained%20financial%20position%26quot%3B%20underlined%20last%20month%20after%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fspicejet-sends-150-cabin-crew-on-leave-without-pay-amid-financial-crisis-6449204%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bdifficult%20decision%20to%20temporarily%20place%20150%20cabin%20crew%20on%20furlough%3C%2Fa%3E%20(leave%20without%20pay)%20for%20three%20months%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20troubled%20airline%20hopes%20to%20raise%20Rs%203%2C000%20crore%20from%20sale%20of%20securities%20to%20qualified%20institutional%20buyers%2C%20for%20which%20it%20has%20set%20a%20floor%20price%20of%20Rs%2064.79%20per%20share.%20A%20discount%20of%20%26quot%3Bnot%20more%20than%20five%20per%20cent%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20floor%20price%2C%20with%20shareholders'%20approval%2C%20may%20be%20offered%20if%20deemed%20fit%2C%20SpiceJet%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProceeds%20from%20this%20sale%20will%20be%20partly%20used%20to%20pay%20statutory%20dues%2C%20including%20those%20listed%20above%2C%20as%20well%20as%20settle%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20outstanding%20liabilities%20of%20creditors%2C%20including%20aircraft%20and%20engine%20lessors...%26quot%3B%20and%20payment%20of%20employee%20dues%20and%20airport-related%20fees%2C%20the%20airline%20told%20the%20stock%20exchange.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%20SpiceJet%20said%20Carlyle%20Group's%20commercial%20aviation%20investment%20and%20servicing%20unit%20would%20write%20off%20Rs%204%20crore%20in%20lease%20arrears%20and%20convert%20Rs%203%20crore%20into%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fspicejet-says-carlyle-aviation-will-write-off-40-million-of-lease-arrears-6536136%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECarlyle%20Aviation%20Will%20Write%20Off%20%2440%20Million%20In%20Lease%20Arrears%3A%20SpiceJet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpiceJet%20expects%20to%20use%20Rs%20601.5%20crore%20-%20including%20Rs%20297.5%20crore%20for%20TDS%20dues%20and%20Rs%20156.4%20crore%20for%20deposit%20of%20outstanding%20PF%20contributions%20-%20to%20clear%20statutory%20dues.%20Rs%20150.3%20crore%20will%20be%20used%20to%20pay%20airport-related%20fees.%20The%20bulk%2C%20though%2C%20has%20been%20set%20aside%20to%20settle%20outstanding%20liabilities%20linked%20to%20aircraft%20and%20engine%20lessors%2C%20engineering%20vendors%2C%20and%20financ