el%20to%20WandaVision%2C%20has%20received%20overwhelmingly%20positive%20reactions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fenglish%2Fagatha-all-along-first-reactions-to-kathryn-hahns-spellbinding-performance-in-marvels-new-series%2Farticleshow%2F113447189.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20Lebanon%20Politics%3A%20Hezbollah%2C%20Iran%20And%20A%20Larger%20Battle%20For%20Hegemony%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELebanon's%20political%20system%20is%20deeply%20entrenched%20in%20sectarian%20divisions.%20The%20country%20is%20a%20confessional%20democracy%2C%20meaning%20that%20key%20political%20and%20military%20positions%20are%20reserved%20for%20representatives%20of%20specific%20religious%20sects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20President%20must%20always%20be%20a%20Maronite%20Catholic%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20a%20Sunni%20Muslim%2C%20and%20the%20Speaker%20of%20the%20Parliament%20a%20Shia%20Muslim.%20While%20the%20Deputy%20Speaker%20of%20Parliament%20and%20the%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20are%20always%20Greek%20Orthodox%20Christians%2C%20the%20Chief%20of%20the%20General%20Staff%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20is%20always%20a%20Druze.%20This%20delicate%20balancing%20act%20extends%20to%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20Lebanese%20Parliament%2C%20which%20maintains%20a%20ratio%20of%206%3A5%20in%20favour%20of%20Christians%20to%20Muslims%20(including%20Druze).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20political%20system%20was%20largely%20imposed%20by%20France%20in%201920%20when%20it%20was%20the%20colonial%20power%20in%20the%20Levant%20region.%20Ironically%2C%20France%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20secular%20nations%20in%20Europe%2C%20created%20a%20state%20system%20in%20Lebanon%20that%20is%20wholly%20dependent%20on%20religious%20identities%2C%20said%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20roots%20of%20this%20system%20lie%20in%20a%20proposal%20from%20the%20Maronite%20Church%2C%20as%20Muslims%2C%20particularly%20the%20Sunnis%2C%20initially%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20separate%20Lebanese%20entity%20and%20preferred%20instead%20to%20merge%20with%20Syria.%20Thus%2C%20the%20state%20that%20emerged%20lacked%20solid%20foundations%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20its%20current%20troubles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Hezbollah%2C%20a%20militant%20group%20backed%20by%20Iran%2C%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20de%20facto%20ruler%20of%20Lebanon%2C%20operating%20with%20more%20power%20and%20influence%20than%20the%20official%20government%20and%20threatening%20all-out%20war%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20a%20series%20of%20explosions%20from%20pagers%20used%20by%20Hezbollah%20members%20in%20Lebanon%20resulted%20in%20at%20least%20nine%20deaths%20and%20approximately%202%2C800%20injuries.%20The%20Iran-backed%20group%20attributed%20the%20blasts%20to%20Israel.%20While%20Israel%20has%20not%20commented%2C%20the%20operation's%20sophistication%20has%20led%20many%20to%20suspect%20the%20involvement%20of%20its%20intelligence%20agency%2C%20Mossad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInside%20Lebanese%20Politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLebanon%20is%20an%20illiberal%20democracy.%20That%20is%2C%20the%20Lebanese%20do%20go%20to%20the%20polls%20fairly%20regularly%2C%20but%20they%20are%20expected%20to%20choose%20from%20a%20set%20of%20pre-determined%20ideas%20that%20do%20not%20interfere%20with%20the%20existing%20structure%20as%20was%20designed%20by%20the%20oligarchs%2C%20and%20now%20taken%20over%20by%20Hezbollah%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hussain%20Abdul-Hussain%2C%20veteran%20journalist%2C%20Middle%20East%20expert%20and%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Foundation%20For%20Defense%20of%20Democracy%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20power-sharing%20arrangement%20that%20forms%20the%20bedrock%20of%20Lebanon's%20government%20is%20not%20just%20an%20outdated%20relic%3B%20it%20is%20a%20carefully%20maintained%20system%20designed%20to%20preserve%20the%20status%20quo.%20The%20shadow%20state%20within%20the%20official%20state%20has%20now%20become%20the%20norm%2C%20with%20the%20real%20power%20held%20not%20by%20elected%20officials%20but%20by%20Hezbollah%20and%20its%20allies.%20The%20militia%20group%2C%20which%20pledges%20allegiance%20to%20Iran's%20Supreme%20Leader%2C%20operates%20outside%20of%20the%20traditional%20state%20structures%20but%20holds%20ultimate%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Lebanons%20capital%20Beirut%20during%20the%201982%20war.%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Lebanons%20capital%20Beirut%20during%20the%201982%20war.%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fs0rudue_beirut-1982-civil-war-_625x300_17_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELebanon's%20capital%20Beirut%20during%20the%201982%20war.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Getty%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuppose%20you%20want%20to%20run%20on%20a%20platform%20that%20demands%20unconditional%20and%20immediate%20peace%20with%20Israel%2C%20you%20will%20either%20be%20disqualified%20or%20suffer%20violence%20by%20non-state%20actors%20(Hezbollah).%20Even%20though%20the%20country%20has%20a%20hybrid%20presidential%2Fparliamentary%20system%2C%20its%20rulers%20have%20been%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20people%20over%20the%20past%2040%20or%20more%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Abdul-Hussain%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20elites%20who%20drafted%20Lebanon's%20constitution%20in%201926%2C%20mainly%20Christian%20business%20leaders%2C%20ensured%20that%20state%20powers%20were%20decentralised%2C%20effectively%20granting%20various%20religious%20sects%20immunity%20from%20state%20prosecution%20and%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20arrangement%20created%20a%20system%20where%20the%20political%20and%20business%20elite%20thrived%20while%20national%20identity%20and%20state%20institutions%20remained%20weak.%20The%20sectarian%20affiliation%20has%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20overridden%20national%20identity%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20fractured%20society%20and%20a%20government%20that%20struggles%20to%20maintain%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHezbollah%3A%20From%20Militia%20To%20De%20Facto%20Ruler%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHezbollah's%20journey%20from%20a%20militia%20group%20to%20Lebanon's%20most%20powerful%20political%20and%20military%20entity%20started%20in%201982%20following%20Israel's%20invasion%20of%20the%20country.%20Initially%20perceived%20as%20a%20resistance%20movement%20against%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20Hezbollah%20has%20since%20transformed%20into%20a%20big%20game%20player%20in%20Lebanese%20politics.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20a%20political%20party%20but%20a%20state%20within%20a%20state%20-%20a%20powerful%20armed%20militia%20that%20supersedes%20the%20Lebanese%20Armed%20Forces%20(LAF)%20in%20strength%20and%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Hezbollah%20chief%20Hassan%20Nasrallah%20during%20one%20of%20his%20televised%20speeches.%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Hezbollah%20chief%20Hassan%20Nasrallah%20during%20one%20of%20his%20televised%20speeches.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F5n0qp8s_hassan-nasrallah-getty-_625x300_17_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHezbollah%20chief%20Hassan%20Nasrallah%20during%20one%20of%20his%20televised%20speeches.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Getty%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHezbollah%20chief%20Hassan%20Nasrallah%20does%20not%20hold%20any%20public%20office%2C%20but%20he%20is%20the%20de%20facto%20ruler%20of%20Lebanon.%20He%20rules%20by%20televised%20speech.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20state%20(even%20when%20there%20was%20a%20president%20and%20prime%20minister)%2C%20learn%20the%20fate%20of%20their%20country%20and%20tailor%20their%20policies%20in%20accordance%20with%20what%20they%20hear%20Nasrallah%20saying%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Abdul-Hussain%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHezbollah's%20Role%20In%20Lebanese%20Government%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20has%20successfully%20infiltrated%20various%20branches%20of%20the%20Lebanese%20government%20and%20security%20apparatus%2C%20ensuring%20its%20interests%20are%20safeguarded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHezbollah%20started%20in%201982%20during%20Israel's%20occupation%20of%20Beirut%2C%20splitting%20from%20the%20original%20Shia%20militia%2C%20Amal%2C%20which%20was%20more%20secular.%20Amal%20and%20Hezbollah%20fought%20for%20turf%20but%20ultimately%20came%20to%20a%20living%20arrangement%20since%20both%20of%20them%20were%20pro-Syria%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nizar%20Farsakh%2C%20lecturer%20at%20the%20Elliott%20School%20of%20International%20Affairs%20at%20George%20Washington%20University%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20both%20were%20active%20in%20the%20resistance%2C%20having%20been%20part%20of%20the%20Palestine%20Liberation%20Organization%20(PLO)%20militias%20before%20getting%20formed%2C%20Hezbollah%20took%20on%20most%20of%20the%20resistance%2C%20effectively%20monopolising%20it%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%201990s%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Israeli%20forces%20invade%20Lebanon%20in%201982.%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Israeli%20forces%20invade%20Lebanon%20in%201982.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F5agshpp8_israeli-troops-invade-lebanon-getty_625x300_17_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20forces%20invaded%20Lebanon%20in%201982.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Getty%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHezbollah%20gained%20widespread%20recognition%20in%20the%202000s%20when%20Israel%20unilaterally%20withdrew%20from%20Lebanon%20after%20years%20of%20resistance.%20This%20victory%20was%20historic%2C%20marking%20the%20first%20time%20an%20Arab%20military%20force%20successfully%20forced%20Israel%20out%20of%20occupied%20territory%2C%20unlike%20Egypt's%20success%2C%20which%20came%20through%20diplomacy%20rather%20than%20combat.%20The%20triumph%20elevated%20Hezbollah's%20status%20not%20only%20in%20Lebanon%20but%20across%20the%20Arab%20and%20Muslim%20worlds%2C%20where%20it%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20resistance%20against%20Israeli%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCoupled%20with%20very%20strong%20relations%20with%20Iran%20and%20Syria%2C%20it%20got%20flooded%20with%20weapons%20and%20got%20extensive%20training%20in%20addition%20to%20creating%20a%20very%20well-oiled%20political%20movement%20that%20was%20theocratically%20totalitarian%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Farsakh%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202006%20Lebanon%20War%20further%20solidified%20Hezbollah's%20role%20as%20a%20key%20player%20in%20the%20region.%20Although%20Israel%20inflicted%20severe%20damage%20on%20Lebanon's%20infrastructure%2C%20Hezbollah's%20ability%20to%20hold%20off%20the%20Israeli%20Defense%20Forces%20(IDF)%20for%20over%20a%20month%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20success%20by%20many%20in%20the%20Arab%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHezbollah's%20power%20was%20again%20demonstrated%20in%202008%20when%20the%20anti-Syrian%20camp%20in%20Lebanon%20attempted%20to%20dismantle%20its%20separate%20telecommunications%20network%2C%20sparking%20a%20brief%20conflict.%20Hezbollah%20quickly%20asserted%20its%20dominance%2C%20establishing%20itself%20as%20the%20de%20facto%20military%20power%20in%20Lebanon.%20This%20marked%20a%20turning%20point%2C%20showing%20that%20no%20force%20in%20Lebanon%20could%20challenge%20Hezbollah's%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20Hezbollah%20members%20are%20MPs%20and%20some%20are%20cabinet%20ministers.%20%C2%A0And%20while%20Lebanon%20has%20a%20mostly%20non-sectarian%20professional%20army%2C%20it%20does%20not%20challenge%20Syria%20nor%20Hezbollah%2C%20and%20the%20two%20coordinate%20to%20ensure%20they%20co-exist%20without%20clashes.%20Some%20Lebanese%20feel%20that%20even%20the%20army%20is%20controlled%20by%20Hezbollah.%20Therefore%2C%20nothing%20happens%20in%20Lebanon%20that%20Hezbollah%20is%20not%20on%20board%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Farsakh%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHezbollah%20vs%20Lebanese%20Armed%20Forces%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20Lebanese%20security%20official%20who%20dared%20to%20defy%20Hezbollah%2C%20Brigadier%20General%20Wissam%20al-Hassan%2C%20was%20assassinated%20after%20exposing%20the%20armed%20group's%20role%20in%20the%202005%20assassination%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Rafic%20Hariri.%20al-Hassan%20was%20the%20chief%20of%20Lebanon's%20intelligence%20agency%20and%20a%20leading%20Sunni%20figure%20in%20the%20country.%20In%202012%2C%20al-Hassan%20was%20killed%20along%20with%20seven%20others%20in%20a%20massive%20car%20bombing%20that%20also%20injured%2080%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20Lebanon%20Prime%20Minister%20Rafic%20hariri%20with%20ex%20US%20President%20George%20Bush%20at%20the%20White%20House.%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Former%20Lebanon%20Prime%20Minister%20Rafic%20hariri%20with%20ex%20US%20President%20George%20Bush%20at%20the%20White%20House.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F36f6jhgo_rafic-hariri-george-bush-getty-_625x300_18_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Lebanon%20Prime%20Minister%20Rafic%20hariri%20with%20ex%20US%20President%20George%20Bush%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Getty%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lebanese%20security%20agencies%2C%20riddled%20with%20Hezbollah%20loyalists%2C%20are%20often%20seen%20as%20mere%20extensions%20of%20Hezbollah's%20influence%20rather%20than%20independent%20state%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHezbollah%20is%20multifold%20and%20more%20powerful%20than%20the%20Lebanese%20Armed%20Forces%20(LAF).%20Hezbollah%20also%20infiltrates%20the%20LAF%20and%20other%20security%20agencies%20by%20planting%20its%20loyalists%20at%20high%20levels.%20These%20security%20agencies%20do%20Hezbollah's%20bidding%2C%20and%20never%20go%20against%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Abdul-Hussain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%201989%20Taif%20Agreement%2C%20which%20ended%20the%20Lebanese%20civil%20war%2C%20the%20LAF's%20role%20has%20increasingly%20been%20to%20counter%20Hezbollah's%20narrative%20that%20it%20alone%20can%20defend%20Lebanon%20against%20external%20threats.%20This%20is%20particularly%20evident%20in%20the%20context%20of%20US%20military%20aid%20to%20the%20LAF%2C%20which%20has%20totalled%20over%20%242.29%20billion%20since%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20Stalemate%3A%20A%20Vacant%20Presidency%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20Lebanon's%20presidential%20post%20is%20vacant%2C%20which%20is%20emblematic%20of%20the%20country's%20political%20paralysis.%20The%20two%20main%20contenders%20for%20the%20presidency%20-%20Gebran%20Bassil%20and%20Suleiman%20Frangieh%20-%20are%20both%20allied%20with%20Hezbollah%2C%20but%20the%20group%20has%20refrained%20from%20endorsing%20either%20candidate%20to%20avoid%20alienating%20one%20faction%20of%20its%20support%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20anti-Hezbollah%20parliamentary%20opposition%20has%20its%20own%20candidates%2C%20but%20even%20if%20it%20manages%20to%20get%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20vote%2C%20Hezbollah%20breaks%20the%20session%20midway.%20The%20speaker%20of%20the%20Lebanese%20assembly%2C%20Nabih%20Berri%2C%20is%20Shia%20like%20Hezbollah%20and%20heads%20the%20Amal%20movement%2C%20a%20Hezbollah%20ally%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Abdul-Hussain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELebanon's%20government%20is%20thus%20paralysed%2C%20unable%20to%20elect%20a%20president%20or%20move%20forward%20on%20critical%20national%20issues.%20This%20paralysis%20is%20compounded%20by%20an%20economic%20crisis%20that%20has%20seen%20the%20country's%20currency%20collapse%20and%20basic%20services%20like%20electricity%20and%20water%20cut%20off%20for%20weeks%20at%20a%20time.%20Yet%20Hezbollah%2C%20impervious%20to%20the%20country's%20plight%2C%20continues%20to%20prepare%20for%20potential%20conflicts%2C%20such%20as%20a%20war%20with%20Israel%2C%20as%20seen%20in%20its%20support%20for%20Hamas%20during%20recent%20regional%20tensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIran%20has%20replicated%20its%20model%20in%20Lebanon%20in%20which%20two%20states%20are%20expected%20to%20coexist%3A%20A%20weak%20official%20state%2C%20usually%20elected%2C%20and%20a%20strong%20shadow%20state%2C%20unelected%20but%20holding%20the%20reigns%20of%20power%20through%20non-state%20militias%20that%20report%20to%20a%20cleric%20Supreme%20Leader.%20In%20Iran%2C%20the%20shadow%20state%20dictates%20routine%20elections.%20In%20Lebanon%2C%20Hezbollah%20always%20balances%20out%20the%20degree%20of%20dictation%20and%20the%20will%20of%20its%20oligarch%20allies.%20Since%20Hezbollah%20is%20allied%20with%20many%20oligarchs%2C%20and%20since%20many%20of%20them%20have%20competing%20interests%2C%20whenever%20there%20is%20a%20deadlock%2C%20the%20Iran-backed%20militia%20refrains%20from%20intervening%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Abdul-Hussain%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMain%20Drivers%20Of%20Conflict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHezbollah's%20position%20as%20the%20dominant%20force%20in%20Lebanese%20politics%20shows%20no%20signs%20of%20weakening%2C%20despite%20economic%20pressures%20and%20dwindling%20financial%20resources%20due%20to%20cuts%20in%20Iranian%20funds%20and%20US%20sanctions.%20The%20U.S.%20considers%20Hezbollah%20not%20only%20a%20regional%20threat%20but%20a%20global%20one%2C%20labelling%20it%20a%20transnational%20criminal%20organization%20due%20to%20its%20extensive%20network%20of%20sleeper%20cells%20across%20continents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20Lebanon%20could%20see%20a%20significant%20shift%20away%20from%20Hezbollah's%20control%20seems%20unlikely.%20Mr%20Abdul-Hussain%20argues%20that%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20full-blown%20conflict%20between%20the%20LAF%20and%20Hezbollah%20are%20slim%2C%20as%20the%20army%20command%20has%20already%20ruled%20out%20initiating%20such%20a%20conflict%20due%20to%20the%20heavy%20human%20and%20political%20toll%20it%20would%20take.%20Instead%2C%20the%20focus%20remains%20on%20containing%20Hezbollah's%20influence%20within%20Lebanon%20through%20economic%20and%20political%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-08%2Fi1hs18f_hezbollah-chief-hassan-nasrallah_625x300_26_August_19.jpg%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTwo%20trends%20have%20been%20competing%20in%20Lebanon%20since%20its%20independence%20in%201948.%20The%20Christian-led%20bloc%20demands%20Lebanese%20regional%20neutrality%20and%20openness%20to%20the%20West.%20The%20Muslim-led%20bloc%20insists%20that%20Lebanon%20should%20be%20involved%20in%20regional%20conflicts%2C%20such%20as%20fighting%20for%20the%20liberation%20of%20Palestine.%20This%20fault%20line%20caused%20a%20civil%20war%20in%201975%2C%20which%20only%20ended%20when%20Muslims%20committed%20that%20Lebanon%20would%20become%20neutral.%20Hezbollah%20never%20agreed%20to%20this%20arrangement%20and%20as%20it%20took%20over%20the%20country%20in%202008%2C%20has%20proven%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Abdul-Hussain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPotential%20Full-Blown%20War%20With%20Israel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20Hezbollah%2C%20and%20Iran%2C%20entered%20Israel's%20ongoing%20conflict%20with%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20frequent%20skirmishes%20along%20the%20Israel-Lebanon%20border%20have%20resulted%20in%20multiple%20deaths%20on%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2