rs%20aged%2013%20to%2017%20from%20the%20mental%20health%20challenges%20often%20linked%20to%20social%20media%20use.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20the%20update%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20and%20authorities%20have%20long%20criticised%20Instagram%20for%20its%20role%20in%20worsening%20mental%20health%20problems%20such%20as%20anxiety%2C%20addiction%2C%20cyberbullying%2C%20eating%20disorders%20and%20low%20self-esteem%2C%20among%20teens.%20Governments%20and%20advocacy%20groups%20around%20the%20world%20have%20called%20for%20stronger%20safeguards.%20Some%2C%20like%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Australia%2C%20are%20setting%20age%20restrictions%20for%20social%20media%20use.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeta%2C%20Instagram's%20parent%20company%2C%20response%20is%20this%20significant%20update%20that%20defaults%20teens'%20accounts%20to%20private%2C%20limits%20who%20can%20contact%20them%2C%20and%20controls%20what%20content%20they%20are%20exposed%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFeatures%20of%20%26quot%3BTeen%20Accounts%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPrivate%20accounts%20-%20Teens%20aged%2013%20to%2017%20will%20have%20their%20accounts%20set%20to%20private%20by%20default%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20strangers%20to%20view%20or%20interact%20with%20their%20profiles.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMessaging%20restrictions%20-%20Direct%20messaging%20(DM)%20will%20have%20tighter%20controls%2C%20allowing%20teens%20to%20receive%20messages%20only%20from%20people%20they%20follow.%20This%20reduces%20the%20chances%20of%20contact%20with%20unwanted%20or%20harmful%20individuals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESensitive%20content%20restrictions%20-%20Teens%20will%20have%20limited%20exposure%20to%20potentially%20harmful%20or%20inappropriate%20content.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELimited%20interactions%20-%20Interaction%20with%20adult%20accounts%20that%20do%20not%20follow%20them%20back%20will%20be%20limited%2C%20reducing%20risks%20like%20unsolicited%20DMs%20or